mwell and the Common Weal\n  |location = Cambridge\n  |publisher = Cambridge University Press\n  |year = 1973\n  |isbn= 978-0521200547\n  |ref={{sfnref|Elton|1973}}\n}}\n* {{Cite book|last = Elton\n  |first = Geoffrey Rudolph\n  |chapter = An Early Tudor Poor Law\n  |title = Studies in Tudor and Stuart Politics and Government\n  |location=London\n  |publisher = Cambridge University Press\n  |volume = II\n  |year = 1974\n  |pages=137\u2013154\n  |chapter-url=http://ebooks.cambridge.org/chapter.jsf?bid=CBO9780511561108&cid=CBO9780511561108A013&tabName=Chapter\n  |doi=10.1017/CBO9780511561108.006\n  |isbn=9780511561108\n  |ref={{sfnref|Elton|1974}}\n}}\n* {{Cite book|last = Elton\n  |first = Geoffrey Rudolph\n  |chapter = King or Minister? The Man behind the Henrician Reformation\n  |title = Studies in Tudor and Stuart Politics and Government\n  |volume = I\n  |location=Cambridge\n  |publisher = Cambridge University Press\n  |year = 1974\n  |pages=173\u2013188\n  |chapter-url=http://ebooks.cambridge.org/chapter.jsf?bid=CBO9780511561092&cid=CBO9780511561092A017&tabName=Chapter\n  |doi=10.1017/CBO9780511561092.010\n  |isbn=9780511561092\n  |ref={{sfnref|Elton|1974|pp=173\u2013188}}\n}}\n* {{Cite book|last = Elton\n  |first = Geoffrey Rudolph\n  |title = Policy and Police: The Enforcement of the Reformation in the Age of Thomas Cromwell\n  |location=Cambridge\n  |publisher = Cambridge University Press\n  |year = 1985\n  |isbn = 9780521313094\n  |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C6o5AAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false\n  |ref={{sfnref|Elton|1985}}\n}}\n* {{Cite book|last = Elton\n  |first = Geoffrey Rudolph\n  |title = England Under the Tudors\n  |publisher = [[Routledge]]\n  |location = London\n  |year = 1991\n  |edition = 3rd\n  |isbn=9780415065337\n  |ref={{sfnref|Elton|1991b}}\n}}\n* Everett, Michael. ''The Rise of Thomas Cromwell: Power and Politics in the Reign of Henry VIII'' (Yale University Press, 2015)\n*{{cite web|url=https://queenanneboleyn.com/2019/08/18/all-that-glitters-hans-holbeins-lady-of-the-cromwell-family-by-teri-fitzgerald/|title=All that Glitters: Hans Holbein's Lady of the Cromwell Family|last1=Fitzgerald|first1=Teri|date=18 August 2019|website=queenanneboleyn.com|accessdate=5 October 2019|ref={{sfnref|Fitzgerald|2019}}}}\n*{{Cite journal|last=Fitzgerald|first=Teri|last2=MacCulloch|first2=Diarmaid|author2-link=Diarmaid MacCulloch|title=Gregory Cromwell: two portrait miniatures by Hans Holbein the Younger|journal=[[The Journal of Ecclesiastical History]]|volume=67|issue=3|pages=587\u2013601|date=2016|doi=10.1017/S0022046915003322|ref={{sfnref|Fitzgerald and MacCulloch|2016}}}}{{subscription}}\n* {{cite book |first=Dorian |last=Gerhold |title=Thomas Cromwell and his Family in Putney and Wandsworth |publisher=Wandsworth Historical Society |location=London |series=Wandsworth Papers |volume=31 |year=2017 |isbn=9780905121406 }}\n* {{cite book|last=Glover |first=Robert |author-link=Robert Glover (officer of arms) |editor1-last=Rylands |editor1-first=John Paul |editor1-link=John Paul Rylands |title=The Visitation of Cheshire in the year 1580, made by Robert Glover, Somerset Herald, for William Flower, Norroy King of Arms: with numerous additions and continuations, including those from the Visitation of Cheshire made in the year 1566 by the same herald : with an appendix containing the Visitation of a part of Cheshire in the year 1533, made by William Fellows, Lancaster Herald, for Thomas Benolte, Clarenceux King of Arms : and a fragment of the Visitation of the city of Chester in the year 1591, made by Thomas Chaloner, Deputy to the Office of Arms |series=Publications of the Harleian Society |volume=18 |location=London |publisher=[[Harleian Society]] |year=1882 |url=https://archive.org/stream/visitationofches00glov#page/128/mode/2up |ref={{sfnref|Glover|1882}}}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hall\n  |first=Edward\n  |author-link=Edward Hall\n  |title=Hall's chronicle; containing the history of England, during 